  "description": "Reliquary Stores forms a sealed basalt vault set behind gasketed bulkheads and ash baffles, constructed to keep the temple’s abrasive dust from fouling its contents. Copper grounding rods and insulated conduit runs band the walls, tying the chamber into the nave’s electrostatic bleed system. Racked alcoves and lock-faced slagcrete cabinets line the perimeter beneath narrow auroraglass slits that cast violet bars across stamped inventory plates. The air remains muffled by vox-silencing insulation, and the floor is laid in vitrified stone scored with drainage channels for ash and grit.",
